H0.text: Compact bone makes up the dense outer layer of bones.

H1.text: Adipose tissue makes up the dense outer layer of bones.

H2.text: Ligaments make up the dense outer layer of bones.

H3.text: Plasma is what makes up the dense outer layer of bones.

A4.text: Cortex of bone is composed of cortical bone, which is also called compact bone as it is much denser than cancellous bone.

A5.text: The cortical bone gives bone its smooth, white, and solid appearance, and accounts for 80% of the total bone mass of an adult human skeleton.
